textDisplay: Isn't it strange that this lens and the fisheye have threading for filters, yet no one will try to manufacture them? It is possible. I mean, look at the tech in the world today. You can't tell me we aren't capable of manufacturing a workable filter for these lenses. They may cause issues at the widest edges, but I think it would be great. My fisheye is torn up, but thankfully the glass is still pretty nice. Just a scratch or two. Still, I always wished it had a UV option at the least, since they don't manufacture it anymore.
textOriginal: Isn't it strange that this lens and the fisheye have threading for filters, yet no one will try to manufacture them? It is possible. I mean, look at the tech in the world today. You can't tell me we aren't capable of manufacturing a workable filter for these lenses. They may cause issues at the widest edges, but I think it would be great. My fisheye is torn up, but thankfully the glass is still pretty nice. Just a scratch or two. Still, I always wished it had a UV option at the least, since they don't manufacture it anymore.
